    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>PJ and his friend, AJ are having a walk in a square field of size <b>N x N</b>. A snake bites AJ at position <b>(N,1)</b> [1-based indexing] and tries to escape; it moves inside the field in a special manner. PJ being quite intellegent, manages to predict where the snake will be at any given point in time. </p>\n<p>\nThe pattern below shows how the snake will move in a 4x4 field. The values in each position are the number of seconds the snake takes to arrive there after biting AJ.</p>\n<p>\n7\u00a0\u00a0\u00a013\u00a0\u00a014\u00a0\u00a0\u00a016<br />\n6\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a08\u00a0\u00a0\u00a012\u00a0\u00a0\u00a015<br />\n2\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a05\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a09\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a011<br />\n1\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a03\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a04\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a010</p>\n<p>\nIf PJ chooses a value of (X, Y) to place a box and capture the snake, can you tell how many seconds after biting AJ, the snake will be at (X, Y)?</p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The first line contains <b>T</b>, the number of test cases. This is followed by T lines, each containing 3 space separated integers: <b>N, X, Y</b>.</p>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>For each test case, output a line containing the time the snake takes to arrive at <b>(X, Y)</b>.</p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>500</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>1000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>X</b> \u2264 <b>N</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>Y</b> \u2264 <b>N</b></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2\n4 2 3\n6 1 5\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n12\n34\n</pre><h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1.</b> Refer to the pattern shown above. The snake is present at position <b>(2,3)</b> at 12 seconds</p>\n",
